{"award_age":42.0,"bio_image":"full\/5cfc0d644e7fb1b164ba34ae55ddfd6b001bd160.jpg","category":"Physics","country":"United States","date_of_birth":"1936-01-10T00:00:00.000Z","date_of_death":null,"gender":"male","image_urls":["http:\/\/upload.wikimedia.org\/wikipedia\/commons\/thumb\/b\/b5\/Wilson_penzias200.jpg\/220px-Wilson_penzias200.jpg"],"link":"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Robert_Woodrow_Wilson","mini_bio":"<p><b>Robert Woodrow Wilson<\/b> (born January 10, 1936) is an <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/United_States\" title=\"United States\">American<\/a> <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Astronomer\" title=\"Astronomer\">astronomer<\/a>, 1978 Nobel laureate in <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Nobel_Prize_in_physics\" title=\"Nobel Prize in physics\" class=\"mw-redirect\">physics<\/a>, who with <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Arno_Allan_Penzias\" title=\"Arno Allan Penzias\">Arno Allan Penzias<\/a> discovered in 1964 the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Cosmic_microwave_background_radiation\" title=\"Cosmic microwave background radiation\" class=\"mw-redirect\">cosmic microwave background radiation<\/a> (CMB). The award purse was also shared with a third scientist, <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Pyotr_Leonidovich_Kapitsa\" title=\"Pyotr Leonidovich Kapitsa\" class=\"mw-redirect\">Pyotr Leonidovich Kapitsa<\/a>, for unrelated work.<\/p><p>While working on a new type of <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Holmdel_Horn_Antenna\" title=\"Holmdel Horn Antenna\">antenna<\/a> at <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Bell_Labs\" title=\"Bell Labs\">Bell Labs<\/a> in <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Holmdel_Township,_New_Jersey\" title=\"Holmdel Township, New Jersey\">Holmdel Township, New Jersey<\/a>, they found a source of noise in the atmosphere that they could not explain.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Robert_Woodrow_Wilson#cite_note-1\"><span>[<\/span>1<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> After removing all potential sources of noise, including pigeon droppings on the antenna, the noise was finally identified as CMB, which served as important corroboration of the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Big_Bang\" title=\"Big Bang\">Big Bang<\/a> theory.<\/p>","name":"Robert Woodrow Wilson","place_of_birth":"Houston, Texas ,  USA","place_of_death":null,"text":"Robert Woodrow Wilson , Physics, 1978","year":1978.0}